# Implementation Plan: Dashboard & Image Upload

## Goal
Make the "Schedule Car" and "Statistics" components on the dashboard use real database data, make their interactive buttons work (including the search bar), and implement an image upload button on the "Car Details" page. Ensure all data flows correctly from Supabase -> Redux -> Frontend.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Overview Dashboard Data Sourcing
- **[src/app/dashboard/page.tsx](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/src/app/dashboard/page.tsx)**
  - Use `useEffect` to dispatch `fetchBookings()` and `fetchCars()` on mount so all child components (Schedule, Statistics, Orders) have access to the full Redux state from the database.

### 2. Schedule Component
- **[src/components/dashboard/ScheduleSection.tsx](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/src/components/dashboard/ScheduleSection.tsx)**
  - Connect to Redux to read `bookings` and `cars` state.
  - Dynamically map `bookings` (with status `confirmed` or `completed`) to the visual timeline rows.
  - Implement **Search Bar** logic: filter the displayed bookings by Car ID, Car Name, or Guest Name based on input.
  - Wire up **Tabs (Day/Week/Month)** and **Arrows (< >)** to control local state and correctly shift the visual mapping span of the timeline.

### 3. Statistics Component
- **[src/components/dashboard/StatisticCard.tsx](file:///d:/car%20rental%20landing%20page/frontend/src/components/dashboard/StatisticCard.tsx)**
  - Implement Shadcn `dropdown-menu` for the "Past 7 days" header button layout.
  - Use `bookings` from Redux to calculate actual total "Customer" count, "Order" count, "Income", and "Expenses".
  - Make the see detail buttons navigate to appropriate dashboard sections.

### 4. Car Image Upload
- **`src/app/dashboard/vehicles/[id]/edit/page.tsx` & `add/page.tsx`**
  - Add an `<input type="file" />` labeled "Upload Image" integrated into the form layout.
  - Add a handler that takes the selected file and either uploads it to a Supabase Storage bucket (if one named `cars` exists) or converts it to a Base64 `TEXT` string to store directly in the `image_url` column. (We will use Supabase Storage if the bucket can be created/accessed, otherwise Base64 for guaranteed persistence).
  - Show a preview of the selected/uploaded image.

## Verification Plan
### Automated & Manual Tests
1. **Manual Check:** Load `/dashboard`, verify Redux DevTools or Console shows `bookings` and `cars` fetched on mount.
2. **Manual Check:** Open Overview Dashboard, confirm "Schedule" populates with the user's booking data instead of the previous hardcoded `Santoso`/`Toyota Avanza`.
3. **Manual Check:** Type a name in the Schedule "Search" bar, verify the list filters correctly.
4. **Manual Check:** Look at "Statistics", confirm Income equals the sum of `total_price` of the bookings.
5. **Manual Check:** Go to "All Vehicles" -> "Edit" a vehicle. Click "Upload Image", select a local picture, save changes, and verify the image updates on the grid and database.
